	<text>
		<body>
				<p>My dear friend&#58;</p>
				<p><del>&#63;</del></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">What shall I say to your complaints and suffering&#63; Am I not<lb/> in a much sadder position&#63; I am completely shut <sic>offnfrom</sic> the world. I<lb/> cannot hold a literary conversation with anybody. That is what is meant<lb/> by&#44; &#8220;He who increases knowledge&#44; increases pain&#8221;. In addition&#44; I feel<lb/> very poorly.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The proof sheets&#45;the second set &#8212; I received only today. I<lb/> have corrected them again but only superficially&#44; so that the first are<lb/> probably more correct. Nevertheless&#44; I send you these because they are<lb/> corrected more neatly.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I did not take the <sic>pentateuch</sic> over. It is too expensive.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I send you cordial greetings.</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Yours sincerely&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Jonah Bondi</persName></p>
				<p rend="&#40;Other side&#41;"></p>
				<p>It is very unpleasant for me not to see printed the entire preface<lb/> and introduction. The few lines on II must&#44; in any event&#44; be printed<lb/> over again. Please do so. With the Hebrew warning&#44; I am not in<lb/> sympathy. At least in <date>January</date>&#44; more will have to be printed&#44; for<lb/> which I shall send you the continuation of the manuscript.</p>
		</body>
